articles.title: Yahoo Finance
articles.content: We previously wrote about five smaller companies that will benefit from the Monetary Authority of Singaporeâ€™s (MAS) S$1.1 billion capital injection to revitalise the Singapore stock market. This money has been assigned to three fund managers who will deploy the funds into smaller, neglected stocks. We decided to dig around and uncovered five more stocks that we believe will benefit from this massive liquidity injection. Revenue rose 7.1% year on year to S$764.7 million while gross profit jumped 9.6% year on year to S$235.6 million.
